snippet: Shares kept up a trend of thin trading and tight moves, with the Standard & Poor’s 500 barely extending its weekly streak of gains to seven.
abstract: Stocks are mixed, lifted by strong report on consumer sentiment but pulled down in late trading by what is said to be an internal report of weak Walmart sales at the start of February 2013.
lead_paragraph: Shares kept up a trend of thin trading and tight moves, with the Standard & Poor’s 500 barely extending its weekly streak of gains to seven.

headline.main: On a Mixed Day, Consumer Sentiment Rises and Wal-Mart Falls
headline.print_headline: Equities End Mixed on Consumer and Sales Reports
